        "cooked": "<p>They wrote <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/pqxdh/\">this blog post</a> two years ago that might help. From what I can find in recent information, Signal uses ML-KEM-1024, but only during the handshake phase of establishing a PQXDH session.</p>\n<p>Edit: official documentation for PQXDH <a href=\"https://signal.org/docs/specifications/pqxdh/\">here</a>.</p>",
